OL,3,CEarly summer heatwave in Europe linked
OL,4,Cto more than 14,000 deaths
OL,6,FEuroMOMO doesn't give absolute numbers
OL,7,Ffor individual countries, but it found
OL,8,Fthe highest rates of excess in France,
OL,9,FBelgium and Germany.
OL,11,FNations that bore the brunt of the
OL,12,Fheat have issued their own estimates,
OL,13,Fwhich don't always follow the same
OL,14,Fmethodology or timelines.
OL,16,FIn the UK, the Met Office said that
OL,17,F2,700 people are believed to have died
OL,18,Ffrom heat-related causes during heat
OL,19,Fwaves in England and Wales in May and
OL,20,FJune.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
