OL,3,CEarly summer heatwave in Europe linked
OL,4,Cto more than 14,000 deaths
OL,6,FIn France, the public health authority
OL,7,Fsaid there were at least 2,000 more
OL,8,Fdeaths in the week of June 22-28 than
OL,9,Fthe previous week, when temperatures
OL,10,Fwere already climbing.
OL,12,FFrance recorded its hottest-ever days
OL,13,Fon June 24 and 25, when the Meteo
OL,14,FFrance weather service said the
OL,15,Fnational thermal indicator ` an
OL,16,Faverage of daily temperatures measured
OL,17,Fat 30 weather stations hit 30C.
OL,19,FMore than 40% of France saw peak
OL,20,Ftemperatures of above 40C.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
